- Server endpoints: core app, session, telemetry, institution, people, students, courses, admin requests, proof sandbox, academic bootstrap, academic proof, runtime, admin offerings, admin control plane

Access hints captured:
- `#/app` is role-driven through the academic workspace helpers
- `#/admin` and the proof/admin deep links are system-admin territory
- Academic bootstrap and proof routes are role-scoped across Course Leader, Mentor, and HoD paths
- Faculty profile access is self, HoD, or system admin

Verification notes:
- Local verification passed: `npm test -- tests/portal-routing.test.ts tests/proof-pilot.test.ts`
- Result: 2 files passed, 15 tests passed
- Live verification was not run in this pass; the route map records the live smoke targets to check next: `#/app`, `#/admin`, and the canonical proof hierarchy

Contradictions:
- No new contradictions were found in this pass
- The pre-existing `C-001` `/health` bootstrap discrepancy remains in the contradiction matrix

If you want, I can do the next audit pass against the same scope and turn this route map into a stricter coverage checklist.
