.md:7:- Any route, role, or feature findings produced before prompt suite `v2.0` should be treated as scaffold-level only until the rerun completes.\\naudit-map/24-agent-memory/known-facts.md:12:- Frontend routing is hash-based at the portal level: `#/` is the chooser, `#/app` is the academic portal, and `#/admin` is the sysadmin portal; academic workspace pages are internal state, while sysadmin deep links extend through `students`, `faculty-members`, `requests`, and the proof-scoped `faculties/.../batches/...` hierarchy.\\naudit-map/24-agent-memory/known-facts.md:31:- The student-shell and risk-explorer routes are indirect drilldown surfaces that remain available to academic roles and `SYSTEM_ADMIN`, but the message/session APIs still enforce active-run and student-scope checks.\\naudit-map/01-inventory/endpoint-index.md:7:- `air-mentor-api/src/modules/academic-admin-offerings-routes.ts`\\naudit-map/01-inventory/endpoint-index.md:9:- `air-mentor-api/src/modules/academic-bootstrap-routes.ts`\\naudit-map/01-inventory/endpoint-index.md:10:- `air-mentor-api/src/modules/academic-proof-routes.ts`\\naudit-map/01-inventory/endpoint-index.md:11:- `air-mentor-api/src/modules/academic-runtime-routes.ts`\\naudit-map/20-prompts/route-map-pass.md:3:Objective: exhaustively map every route-like entry point in the scoped surface, including URL routes, hash routes, helper-generated routes, internal page-state routes, deep links, redirects, guards, restore-on-refresh behavior, query/hash state, modal-triggered routes, and route-conditioned subviews.\\naudit-map/20-prompts/route-map-pass.md:7:- current route index and inventory\\naudit-map/20-prompts/route-map-pass.md:14:- route entries using `templates/route-entry-template.md` or equivalent route tables\\naudit-map/20-prompts/route-map-pass.md:15:- explicit canonical routes, redirect routes, dynamic routes, guarded routes, and hidden entry points\\naudit-map/20-prompts/route-map-pass.md:16:- route-affecting state sources: query para