efresh drift\\naudit-map/20-prompts/live-behavior-pass.md:22:- live verification is not complete until each scoped route or endpoint family has either direct live evidence or an explicit credential or environment blocker\\naudit-map/20-prompts/feature-atom-pass.md:23:- if the same visible feature behaves differently by role, route, active run, or checkpoint context, record separate variants\\naudit-map/20-prompts/prompt-change-log.md:8:| 2026-04-15 | route-map-pass.md, role-surface-pass.md, feature-atom-pass.md, dependency-pass.md, data-flow-pass.md, state-flow-pass.md, ml-audit-pass.md, test-gap-pass.md, ux-friction-pass.md, live-behavior-pass.md, audit-the-audit-pass.md, synthesis-pass.md | Upgraded pass prompts to v2.0 with explicit exhaustiveness and evidence requirements | Prevent shallow route, role, feature, state, and live mapping |\\naudit-map/31-queues/audit-air-mentor-ui-bootstrap-inventory-pass.prompt.md:23:Objective: enumerate the scoped files, routes, scripts, configs, and evidence sources without over-interpreting behavior.\\naudit-map/20-prompts/inventory-pass.md:3:Objective: enumerate the scoped files, routes, scripts, configs, and evidence sources without over-interpreting behavior.\\naudit-map/20-prompts/audit-the-audit-pass.md:10:- coverage diff by route, role, feature, dependency, data, state, ML, test, UX, and live evidence family\\naudit-map/20-prompts/role-surface-pass.md:9:- route guards, data-visibility rules, backend authorization rules, and cross-role truth-coupling notes\\nair-mentor-api/src/lib/msruas-proof-control-plane.ts:842:  let hash = 2166136261\\nair-mentor-api/src/lib/msruas-proof-control-plane.ts:844:    hash ^= char.charCodeAt(0)\\nair-mentor-api/src/lib/msruas-proof-control-plane.ts:845:    hash = Math.imul(hash, 16777619)\\nair-mentor-api/src/lib/msruas-proof-control-plane.ts:847:  return (hash >>> 0) / 4294967295\\naudit-map/23-coverage/review-status-by-path.md:5:| `src/` | Mapped | Frontend hash routes and internal navigation entry points cataloged |\\naudit-map/23-coverage/review-status-by-path.md:6:| `src/pages/` | Mapped | Page module inventory captured; route behavior mapping completed |\\naudit-map/23-coverage/review-status-by-path.md:8:| `air-mentor-api/src/` | Mapped | Backend topology known; endpoint and inference audit completed for route families |\\naudit-map/23-coverage/review-status-by-path.md:11:| `air-mentor-api/src/modules/` | Mapped | Route module inventory captured; route and guard mapping completed |\\naudit-map/24-agent-memory/working-knowledge.md:13:- Prompt suite `v1.x` was too weak to force near-lossless route, role, and feature decomposition. Prompt suite `v2.0` now requires exhaustive micro-interaction, state-family, and completeness gating, and the earlier route/role/feature outputs should be treated as provisional.\\naudit-map/24-agent-memory/working-knowledge.md:17:1. rerun `route-map-pass`, `role-surface-pass`, `feature-atom-pass`, and `dependency-pass` under prompt suite `v2.0`\\naudit-map/24-agent-memory/working-knowledge.md:18:2. rebuild final maps so they reflect exhaustive route families, role surfaces, and control-level feature atoms rather than scaffold summaries\\naudit-map/23-coverage/coverage-ledger.md:7:| Route map pass | Superseded scaffold; rerun required | `audit-map/15-final-maps/route-map.md`, `tests/portal-routing.test.ts`, `tests/proof-pilot.test.ts` | 2026-04-15 | v1 prompt mapped major route families but did not force exhaustive redirects, route-state sources, nested route variants, or restore behavior; rerun under prompt v2.0 is queued |\\naudit-map/23-coverage/coverage-ledger.md:8:| Role surface pass | Superseded scaffold; rerun required | `audit-map/15-final-maps/role-feature-matrix.md`, `src/App.tsx`, `src/system-admin-live-app.tsx`, `air-mentor-api/src/modules/session.ts`, `air-mentor-api/src/modules/academic.ts`, `air-mentor-api/src/modules/academic-proof-routes.ts`, `air-mentor-api/src/modules/academic-runtime-routes.ts`, `air-m